# RDF 2.1.0 Release Notes

## What's New
- **GitHub Issue Model v2** — phase-level tracking replaces per-task issue management,
  reducing API calls by ~72% per release cycle
- **Roadmap Planning** — new `type:initiative` issues for directional time-boxed planning,
  `type:release` issues for versioned release tracking
- **Two-Horizon Roadmap** — Planning Roadmap (Target Date) for big-picture initiatives,
  Execution Roadmap (Release iteration) for active work
- **Task Progress via Comments** — agents post one comment per completed task on the phase
  issue, providing async visibility from any terminal
- **Initiative Lifecycle** — Planning → Specced → Executing → Complete, with cross-project
  initiative support
- **Ecosystem Board Cleanup** — task-level items removed, board now shows phase-level signal
  plus initiative roadmap items
- New Mermaid diagrams: Issue Hierarchy and Two-Horizon Roadmap

## Agent/Command Updates
- `mgr` command gains GitHub integration section for v2 workflow
- `sys-eng` command posts task-completion comments, references phase issues in commits
- `sys-qa` command posts QA verdicts as phase issue comments
- `sys-sentinel` agent posts findings summary on phase issues
- `refresh` command syncs initiative and release issues (removed task issue sync)
- `rel-prep`, `rel-ship`, `rel-merge` updated for type:release lifecycle
- `ecosystem-init` now idempotent (updates fields on existing projects)

## CLI Changes
- `_LABEL_TAXONOMY` gains `type:initiative` and `type:release`
- `_github_ecosystem_init()` adds `Target Date` (DATE) field, `geoscope` project option
- `_github_ecosystem_init()` no longer early-returns on existing project
- Field creation loop handles DATE type (not just SINGLE_SELECT)

## Documentation
- README, RDF.md, WORKFORCE.md updated for v2 model
- Core governance issue conventions rewritten
- Diagrams 7-10 updated/added
- v1 spec Section 5 marked as superseded

## Migration from 2.0.0
No breaking changes. Run `rdf generate claude-code` to pick up canonical updates.
Board cleanup (removing task items) was performed during this release.
